DataElement.preferredName: Case Report Form Study Questionnaire Absent Yes No Indicator
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the yes/no indicator related to a case report form with information regarding a study questionnaire being missing or absent.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Case Report Form Study Questionnaire Absent
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to a case report form (a document designed to record all of the clinical study-required information stipulated in the protocol to be reported to the sponsor on each clinical trial subject) with data regarding a study questionnaire being missing or absent.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A printed, optical, or electronic document designed to record all of the clinical study-required information stipulated in the protocol to be reported to the sponsor on each trial subject.

Concepts.definition: A printed, optical, or electronic document designed to record all of the clinical study-required information stipulated in the protocol to be reported to the sponsor on each clinical trial subject.

Property.preferredDefinition: A detailed examination, analysis, or critical inspection of a subject designed to discover facts about it; the activities undertaken during a study.:Predetermined sets of questions used to collect data - clinical data, social status, occupational group, etc. The term is often applied to a self-completed survey instrument.:Not existing in a specified place at a specified time.

Concepts.definition: A detailed examination, analysis, or critical inspection of a subject designed to discover facts about it.
Not existing in a specified place at a specified time.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: the management of a research protocol and its case report forms.
